description.p:
100 g of the resulting granules were then calcined in a horizontal rotary kiln with an isothermally heated quartz bulb volume of 1 l and a rotary speed of 12 revolutions per minute.


The calcination conditions were as follows:


1st step: the granules used were continuously heated from 25 to 275 (degree)  C. within 50 minutes;


2nd step: the granules used were continuously heated from 275 to 325 (degree)  C. within 30 minutes;


3rd step: the granules used were kept at 325 (degree)  C. for 4 hours;


4th step: the granules used were continuously heated from 325 to 400 (degree)  C. within 30 minutes;


5th step: the granules used were kept at 400 (degree)  C. for 10 minutes.
